# Copy to .env only when you need local overrides.
# The starter service runs without secrets.

RUST_LOG=info
APP_BIND=127.0.0.1:3000

# Agent routing ladder (#4, decision 0001). Both unset → rules-only ladder,
# byte-identical to the pre-ladder platform. LOCAL_MODEL_URL: an in-VPC
# OpenAI-compatible endpoint (vLLM, llama.cpp, LM Studio) — the local tier.
# FRONTIER_MODEL_URL: the frontier rung (Phase 0: test double / in-VPC proxy
# only; the real ClaudeDriver lands behind this rung). Plain http:// only —
# refusing TLS is refusing off-VPC by construction. Offline endpoints degrade
# to rejected attempts and the rules floor still lands the doctor's edit.
# LOCAL_MODEL_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080
# FRONTIER_MODEL_URL=

# Source-workspace treatments and candidate patches. The default is fully
# deterministic and performs no network calls. Hosted environments can opt
# into a private DigitalOcean Gemma endpoint for treatment planning. Candidate
# generation stays deterministic unless a separate worker endpoint is set.
# Every hosted output is revalidated by Rust and falls back locally when the
# provider is unavailable.
# WORKSPACE_AGENT_PROVIDER=digitalocean
# DIGITALOCEAN_PLANNER_ENDPOINT=https://your-private-gemma-endpoint
# DIGITALOCEAN_PLANNER_ACCESS_KEY=store-this-in-the-deployment-secret-store
# DIGITALOCEAN_GENERATOR_ENDPOINT=https://your-deployed-worker-endpoint
# WORKSPACE_AGENT_TIMEOUT_SECS=45
# WORKSPACE_AGENT_MAX_RESPONSE_BYTES=600000

# Optional proof metadata for your evidence index.
PROOF_WORKLOAD=deterministic_api
PROOF_MANAGED_DEFAULT=Supabase or Cloudflare first
PROOF_RUST_BOUNDARY=replay, correctness, async state, or traceable proof

# Clerk is optional. Leave these unset to run the local developer mode.
# In hosted environments, use a separate Clerk instance and subject map for
# staging and production. Keep every value in the deployment secret store.
# CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_or_live_...
# CLERK_ISSUER=https://your-instance.clerk.accounts.dev
# CLERK_JWKS_URL=https://your-instance.clerk.accounts.dev/.well-known/jwks.json
# CLERK_AUTHORIZED_PARTIES=https://staging.example.com
# CLERK_SUBJECT_MAP=user_clerk_subject=staging-test-owner
# ANON_SESSION_HMAC_KEY=generate-at-least-32-random-bytes
